<h2 id="aottext-short-help">Aottext Short-help</h2>
<h4 id="purpose-of-aottext">Purpose of Aottext</h4>
<p>Aottext (Aot means always on top) was made to save pieces of text, a
little like a single Sticky-note.<br />
The text can be shown in 3 different window positions.<br />
Example of usage:</p>
<ul>
<li>horizontally oriented window</li>
<li>vertically oriented window</li>
<li>a small window as the &quot;hidden&quot; position</li>
<li>totally hidden<br />
The entered content is saved automatically, the filename is constructed
from date/time.</li>
</ul>
<h4 id="aottext-usage">Aottext usage</h4>
<table>
<thead>
<tr class="header">
<th>Key(s) / Button</th>
<th>Operation</th>
<th>Remarks</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr class="odd">
<td>[SMode] button</td>
<td>&quot;small&quot; position</td>
<td></td>
</tr>
<tr class="even">
<td>[NMode] button</td>
<td>&quot;normal&quot; position</td>
<td></td>
</tr>
<tr class="odd">
<td>[VMode] button</td>
<td>&quot;vertical&quot; position</td>
<td></td>
</tr>
<tr class="even">
<td>[Exit] button</td>
<td>close the app (content is auto-saved) and reopen it later. :-)</td>
<td></td>
</tr>
<tr class="odd">
<td>[Mouseover] edit field</td>
<td>return to &quot;NMode&quot;</td>
<td>if &quot;SMode&quot; is active</td>
</tr>
<tr class="even">
<td>[Left-shift] + [Right-mousebutton]</td>
<td>toggle &quot;NMode&quot; - &quot;SMode&quot;</td>
<td>pressed anywere on the screen</td>
</tr>
<tr class="odd">
<td>[Control] + [Right-mousebutton]</td>
<td>toggle &quot;NMode&quot; - &quot;VMode&quot;</td>
<td>pressed anywere on the screen</td>
</tr>
<tr class="even">
<td>[Alt] + [a]</td>
<td>toggle hide/show Aottext</td>
<td>always returns to &quot;NMode&quot;</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<h4 id="hide-the-aottext-window-autosmall">Hide the Aottext window:
Autosmall</h4>
<p>If &quot;Settings&quot; -&gt; &quot;Enable Autosmall&quot; is selected,<br />
the Aottext-window is automatically moved/resized to the
&quot;hidden&quot;-position,<br />
if it is <strong>out of focus</strong>.</p>
<h4 id="content-autosave">Content autosave</h4>
<p>Content is saved (if it was changed only!) and:</p>
<ul>
<li>on any &quot;hide&quot;-operation,</li>
<li>on exiting the app.</li>
<li>by pressing the &quot;Op -&gt; Save&quot; button, the content is always saved,
regardless of whether it has been changed.</li>
</ul>
<h4 id="file-history">File history</h4>
<p>Use [Shift] + [Mousewheel] to cycle thru the history (if the
Aottext-window has the focus!).</p>
<h4 id="vmode-button">VMode-button</h4>
<p>VMode moves the Aottext-window to the VMode-position, I use the right
screen side and a verical oriented window.<br />
Gives a better overview, if you want to copy multible lines of text.</p>
<h4 id="smode-and-exit">SMode and EXIT</h4>
<p>Are context sensitiv buttons.<br />
If menu [Op] -&lt; [Settings] -&lt; [Edit Config] is selected, the
functionallity is chanced to &quot;SAVE&quot; and &quot;CANCEL&quot;.</p>
